Sentencas: The precursors of La0.7Sr0.3 - xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3 - delta(LSCCF, x =0.05, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20) as the cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (ITSOFC) were prepared by reverse titration co-precipitation method with metal-nitrates as starting materials and mixed alkali (NaOH and Na2CO3) as a precipitating agent.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of cathode materials La0.7Sr0.3-xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3-δ by reverse titration co-precipitation method for ITSOFC

Sentencas: The formation process of LSCCF from the precursors was monitored by TG-DSC, and the crystal structure and particles morphology of the precursors which were calcined at 600, 800, 1000 degrees C for 3 h were characterized using XRD, SEM technologies.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of cathode materials La0.7Sr0.3-xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3-δ by reverse titration co-precipitation method for ITSOFC

Sentencas: Compared with the solid state reaction of constituent oxides, when the pH value of the precipitating solution was in the range of 9.1 similar to 9.5, the LSCCF powders from the precursors caclined at 800 degrees C for 3 h had high purity, homogeneous and single perovskite phase.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of cathode materials La0.7Sr0.3-xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3-δ by reverse titration co-precipitation method for ITSOFC

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the LSCCF samples sintered at 1200 degrees C for 3 h, which was measured as a function of temperatures from 100 to 800 degrees C by DC four-probe method in air, decreased with x from 0.05 to 0.20.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of cathode materials La0.7Sr0.3-xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3-δ by reverse titration co-precipitation method for ITSOFC

Sentencas: The value of electrical conductivity was almost equal because of Ca2+, Sr2+ co-dopant resulting in the mix effect while x = 0.10 or 0.15.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of cathode materials La0.7Sr0.3-xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3-δ by reverse titration co-precipitation method for ITSOFC

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of all doped samples was higher than 100 S.cm(-1) at intermediate temperatures from 500 to 800 degrees C, and there was good compatibility between the LSCCF cathode and Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 electrolyte.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of cathode materials La0.7Sr0.3-xCaxCo0.9Fe0.1O3-δ by reverse titration co-precipitation method for ITSOFC
